headline: Labcorp (LH) Net Margin Surges to 6.2%, Reinforcing Bullish Earnings Turnaround Narrative
summary: Labcorp Holdings (LH) posted a net profit margin of 6.2% for the period, up from 3.4% a year ago, as earnings surged 96.4% year-over-year. This is well above the company's five-year average despite a longer-term earnings decline of 30.6% per year. Shares sit at $248.14, notably below the estimated fair value of $557.86. The current price-to-earnings ratio of 24.1x is higher than peer and industry averages. Investors are eyeing a potential turnaround as earnings are forecast to grow 14% per...
